A teenager who was shot in the neck by his nine-year-old cousin is today in hospital in a stable condition.

Anas Jaber, 16, was playing video games at his family's home in St Petersburg, Florida, on Saturday when his young relative pointed a gun at him.

The weapon, which the boy had found in the house, went off as Anas raised his hand and told him to put it down.

