Police spokesman Mike Puetz said officers found two rifles in the residence.

He said: 'As the victim raised his hand and told the cousin to put the gun down, the gun discharged striking the victim in the neck and left hand.

'Officers recovered two rifles from the residence and the investigation continues as to the ownership of the weapons and who had responsibility for securing them.'

No charges have been filed.

